Two Walter Sisulu Municipality councillors were arrested by the Hawks on Tuesday for corruption charges after they allegedly sold an RDP house to a member of the public for R150 000.  Ward 7 councillor Mxolisi Mdumisa, 37, and ward 10 councillor Moahlodi Mokhoabane, 54, appeared briefly at the Aliwal North Magistrateâ€™s Court and were released on R1 000 bail. Eastern Cape Hawks provincial spokeswoman Captain Anelisa Feni said the councillors would appear again in the same court on June 12.